OL,5, Lidl is the latest supermarket to      
OL,6, introduce limits on sales of certain   
OL,7, fruit and vegetables due to shortages  
OL,8, of fresh produce.                      
OL,10,FThe company is putting limits of three 
OL,11,Fper customer on sales of peppers,      
OL,12,Ftomatoes and cucumbers, due to "a      
OL,13,Frecent increase in demand".            
OL,15,FIt follows similar moves by Tesco,     
OL,16,FAldi, Asda and Morrisons, with some    
OL,17,Fconsumers facing empty shelves.        
OL,19,FSupermarkets are facing problems after 
OL,20,Fextreme weather hit harvests abroad.   
